00:39:38.918 --> 00:39:40.920
Yes, I love the cool breeze.

00:39:44.716 --> 00:39:46.092
Goodness. Just a moment.

00:39:48.678 --> 00:39:50.597
- Hi.
- <i>Where are you?</i>

00:39:51.973 --> 00:39:53.224
Me?

00:39:54.475 --> 00:39:55.685
I'm on a date.

00:39:56.227 --> 00:39:59.439
<i>You picked the perfect day.</i>
<i>Mom wants to go to my house now.</i>

00:40:00.023 --> 00:40:02.400
- What? Now?
<i>- Yes.</i>

00:40:02.483 --> 00:40:05.570
She wants to go drag Seokkyung home
in case she runs away.

00:40:05.653 --> 00:40:07.280
This won't do. Come right away.

00:40:10.158 --> 00:40:12.911
But I'm out far away.

00:40:12.994 --> 00:40:14.829
<i>What do we do then?</i>

00:40:14.913 --> 00:40:17.332
I need you there stuck next to Seokkyung.

00:40:17.415 --> 00:40:20.919
If she's told to go home now,
she might really change her mind.

00:40:22.754 --> 00:40:25.423
Jeez. Okay, let's hang up for now.

00:40:43.191 --> 00:40:44.192
Hi.

00:40:50.365 --> 00:40:52.867
Hello? Seokkyung.
Where are you? At Seokhee's?

00:40:52.951 --> 00:40:54.452
<i>Yes, I'm at Seokhee's.</i>

00:40:54.535 --> 00:40:56.371
Congrats. I hear you're going back today.

00:40:56.454 --> 00:40:59.248
<i>You made a great decision.</i>

00:40:59.332 --> 00:41:00.416
- What?
<i>- You did.</i>

00:41:00.500 --> 00:41:03.127
- My mom's coming tomorrow.
<i>- I just talked to Seokcheol.</i>

00:41:03.211 --> 00:41:04.879
Your mother is coming today.

00:41:04.963 --> 00:41:05.964
What?

00:41:06.047 --> 00:41:08.174
<i>I'm on my way too.</i>
<i>It'll take about 30 minutes.</i>

00:41:08.257 --> 00:41:09.342
Why are you coming?

00:41:09.425 --> 00:41:13.680
Seokcheol asked me to stay glued to you
as if I was arresting a criminal

00:41:13.763 --> 00:41:15.431
in case you changed your mind.

00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:19.018
You don't have to come.

00:41:19.102 --> 00:41:23.147
<i>What are you talking about?</i>
<i>I have to go, for your safe return.</i>

00:41:23.231 --> 00:41:27.360
You're too scared of your father to go.
You'll be fine if you go with me.

00:41:27.443 --> 00:41:30.321
<i>I doubt he'll break your leg</i>
<i>in my presence.</i>

00:41:30.405 --> 00:41:32.115
<i>- And if he still tries,</i>

00:41:32.198 --> 00:41:34.993
<i>lock the doors and stay in your room.</i>
<i>I'll stop him somehow.</i>

00:41:35.076 --> 00:41:36.411
I'll see you later. Bye.

00:41:45.044 --> 00:41:47.005
<i>Seokkyung is going back home today.</i>

00:41:47.088 --> 00:41:48.089
- Really?
- Yes.

00:41:48.172 --> 00:41:49.257
That's great.

00:41:49.340 --> 00:41:51.467
Shouldn't you go home, then?

00:41:51.551 --> 00:41:52.969
No.

00:41:53.970 --> 00:41:55.346
Let me be free

00:41:55.430 --> 00:41:58.182
from all my family businesses
at least for today.

00:41:58.266 --> 00:41:59.434
I'd love that.

00:42:42.894 --> 00:42:44.812
Oh, goodness.

00:42:48.858 --> 00:42:50.485
Hello, ma'am.

00:42:50.568 --> 00:42:53.321
Hi, Kihong.
Sorry we have to meet on a day like today.

00:42:53.404 --> 00:42:55.948
No, I should be here
on a good day like today.

00:42:56.032 --> 00:42:57.658
- Please get in.
- Thanks.

00:42:57.742 --> 00:42:58.951
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi.

00:42:59.952 --> 00:43:01.871
- Where's Dad?
- He stepped outside.

00:43:03.081 --> 00:43:04.874
We'll bring Seokkyung back home
without him?

00:43:04.957 --> 00:43:07.043
It's better than him
slamming the doors in her face.

00:43:07.919 --> 00:43:10.546
If we get her in the house
while your dad's away,

00:43:10.630 --> 00:43:12.298
he won't be able to drag her out.

00:43:12.840 --> 00:43:14.092
All right. Let's go.

00:43:14.175 --> 00:43:16.010
Okay, let's take off.

00:43:36.906 --> 00:43:37.990
All right.

00:43:45.123 --> 00:43:46.541
Seokkyung, I'm here.

00:43:46.624 --> 00:43:48.668
Do you have a lot to carry?
I'll come up if you do.

00:43:48.751 --> 00:43:50.711
<i>It's not a lot.</i>

00:43:50.795 --> 00:43:52.255
I'll wait down here, then.

00:43:52.338 --> 00:43:54.674
<i>Wait a bit. I need to fix my makeup.</i>

00:43:54.757 --> 00:43:56.134
Okay. Hurry down.

00:44:15.361 --> 00:44:17.780
You look much younger
than before.

00:44:19.323 --> 00:44:22.368
And you've become better with your words.
Now you know how to flatter.

00:44:22.451 --> 00:44:23.703
Oh, please.

00:44:23.786 --> 00:44:25.913
How could you let me see you this way?

00:44:26.330 --> 00:44:29.500
You should visit your future father-in-law
from time to time.

00:44:30.084 --> 00:44:32.670
What are you talking about
all of a sudden?

00:44:32.753 --> 00:44:33.921
What, am I wrong?

00:44:34.005 --> 00:44:35.631
You're right, ma'am.

00:44:35.715 --> 00:44:36.716
I mean, Mother.

00:44:38.968 --> 00:44:40.928
Goodness. I have as many as two daughters,

00:44:41.012 --> 00:44:43.055
but it's so hard
to become a mother-in-law.

00:44:44.390 --> 00:44:47.101
I'll visit you more often
from now on, Mother.

00:44:49.979 --> 00:44:51.522
I'll drive you safely, Mother!

00:44:52.315 --> 00:44:54.567
Thanks.

00:45:08.122 --> 00:45:10.666
She's taking too long to fix her makeup.

00:45:12.043 --> 00:45:13.836
It can't be.

00:45:13.920 --> 00:45:16.672
It can't be. Goodness, no way.

00:45:17.506 --> 00:45:19.508
Why do I keep having this bad feeling?

00:45:20.635 --> 00:45:22.637
Maybe I should quit being a detective.

00:45:24.889 --> 00:45:25.890
Seok...

00:45:27.016 --> 00:45:28.017
Jeez!

00:45:35.066 --> 00:45:36.484
Seokkyung!

00:45:38.694 --> 00:45:40.029
Seokkyung!

00:45:40.112 --> 00:45:41.197
Goodness gracious.

00:45:52.792 --> 00:45:54.252
BYEONGSOO

00:46:23.030 --> 00:46:25.283
- One ticket to Jeongseon.
- Jeongseon, sure.

00:46:25.366 --> 00:46:27.994
- The earliest one, please.
- Okay.

00:46:45.886 --> 00:46:48.306
Mom. It has a nice view.

00:46:49.015 --> 00:46:51.017
- But too many stairs.
- Watch the stairs.

00:46:51.100 --> 00:46:52.977
What the...

00:46:54.145 --> 00:46:58.024
<i>I'm sorry, Byeongsoo.</i>
<i>Don't look for me.</i>

00:46:58.107 --> 00:47:00.109
<i>- Thanks for everything.</i>
- What the...

00:47:00.693 --> 00:47:03.321
- Byeongsoo.
- Oh... Oh! Ma... Ma'am!

00:47:03.404 --> 00:47:05.823
A text?

00:47:05.906 --> 00:47:07.325
You're here too.

00:47:08.075 --> 00:47:11.620
<i>Mom, take care of Hyeonggeun</i>
<i>for me for one more year.</i>

00:47:11.704 --> 00:47:14.665
<i>I'm too ashamed to face you now.</i>
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

00:47:14.749 --> 00:47:16.208
This crazy wench!

00:47:16.292 --> 00:47:19.962
<i>Seokhee,</i>
<i>I'm wearing your socks. Sorry.</i>

00:47:20.379 --> 00:47:22.673
<i>Spend time freely with Kihong</i>
<i>at your place now.</i>

00:47:22.757 --> 00:47:24.550
She's out of her mind.

00:47:24.633 --> 00:47:26.260
- Goodness.
- Mother!

00:47:26.344 --> 00:47:28.095
- Mom.
- What's wrong?

00:47:28.179 --> 00:47:29.805
I don't know, punk.

00:47:30.431 --> 00:47:32.141
Hurry in first.

00:47:32.224 --> 00:47:33.225
Byeongsoo.

00:47:44.904 --> 00:47:48.032
<i>Seokcheol, I...</i>

00:48:16.602 --> 00:48:18.687
- Gosh, I'm so full.
- Me too.

00:48:20.606 --> 00:48:22.566
Would you like
some aromatic scorched-rice water?

00:48:22.650 --> 00:48:25.486
Oh, we're actually too full.

00:48:25.569 --> 00:48:26.987
- But thank you.
- Thank you.

00:48:28.614 --> 00:48:30.991
- I can't eat anymore.
- Same here.

00:48:33.327 --> 00:48:35.079
SEOKKYUNG

00:48:39.583 --> 00:48:40.584
You won't pick up?

00:48:44.630 --> 00:48:45.631
I should.

00:48:52.138 --> 00:48:54.181
- Seokkyung?
- <i>Hey.</i>

00:48:55.599 --> 00:48:56.600
<i>Seokcheol.</i>

00:48:57.518 --> 00:48:58.894
I'm listening.

00:49:00.020 --> 00:49:01.647
I'm not going home.

00:49:03.315 --> 00:49:04.442
I can't bring myself to.

00:49:08.904 --> 00:49:09.905
I'm sorry.

00:49:12.491 --> 00:49:14.994
<i>I thought I should tell you.</i>

00:49:16.912 --> 00:49:18.372
It's too much for me.

00:49:20.249 --> 00:49:21.250
You know, right?

00:49:23.586 --> 00:49:25.504
Yes, I know.

00:49:26.922 --> 00:49:27.923
I'm sorry.

00:49:30.009 --> 00:49:31.510
At least you are.

00:49:34.472 --> 00:49:37.433
<i>If you want to leave and go far away,</i>
<i>go ahead and do that.</i>

00:49:39.477 --> 00:49:42.605
<i>Instead, let me know from time to time</i>

00:49:43.439 --> 00:49:44.690
<i>that you're doing well.</i>

00:49:47.234 --> 00:49:48.235
<i>But...</i>

00:49:49.069 --> 00:49:51.030
<i>if you suddenly feel like coming back,</i>

00:49:52.823 --> 00:49:54.033
don't ignore it,

00:49:55.868 --> 00:49:57.119
because it means that

00:49:58.329 --> 00:50:00.873
one of us is missing you.

00:50:05.920 --> 00:50:07.421
That's family, you know.

00:50:13.886 --> 00:50:15.596
I feel bad for Hyeonggeun.

00:50:17.348 --> 00:50:19.099
The world has lots of good moms...

00:50:19.934 --> 00:50:22.728
...but out of them all,
I happened to be his mom.

00:50:34.740 --> 00:50:35.741
I need to go.

00:50:39.286 --> 00:50:40.454
Okay, go on.

00:50:41.956 --> 00:50:44.500
Call me if something happens, okay?

00:50:48.212 --> 00:50:49.296
Bye.

00:50:49.922 --> 00:50:50.923
Bye.

00:51:13.195 --> 00:51:17.700
<i>Family can be a burden</i>
<i>or a strength sometimes.</i>

00:51:18.867 --> 00:51:21.620
<i>Tearfully, my sister said</i>
<i>she couldn't return home.</i>

00:51:22.913 --> 00:51:23.998
<i>Perhaps</i>

00:51:25.082 --> 00:51:26.959
<i>family couldn't be her strength.</i>

00:51:27.793 --> 00:51:28.794
<i>Or perhaps</i>

00:51:29.545 --> 00:51:32.214
<i>she didn't want to be a burden herself.</i>

00:51:33.048 --> 00:51:34.925
We're leaving in one minute.

00:51:42.474 --> 00:51:44.685
MOM

00:51:48.689 --> 00:51:50.691
HORRIBLE WENCH

00:52:13.088 --> 00:52:14.548
POWER OFF

00:52:18.469 --> 00:52:19.845
We're leaving.

00:52:40.574 --> 00:52:42.451
- Just drop us off here.
- Okay.

00:52:42.534 --> 00:52:44.411
- My dad might be asleep.
- Got it.

00:52:57.049 --> 00:52:59.843
I'll sleep over here tonight.
You can go home.

00:52:59.927 --> 00:53:00.928
Okay.

00:53:01.428 --> 00:53:02.429
Thank you.

00:53:02.846 --> 00:53:06.141
Go in and get some good rest for now.

00:53:06.892 --> 00:53:07.893
Bye.

00:53:12.648 --> 00:53:14.733
Don't show it to your father.

00:53:15.317 --> 00:53:17.236
Tell him we had dinner together.

00:53:17.319 --> 00:53:18.404
Of course.

00:53:35.129 --> 00:53:36.213
Dad!

00:53:37.339 --> 00:53:39.007
Wait. Hey, you...

00:53:39.091 --> 00:53:41.885
Hey, hey, hey.

00:53:41.969 --> 00:53:43.178
Have you been well?

00:53:43.262 --> 00:53:46.640
Stop this. You're a grown-up woman.

00:53:46.724 --> 00:53:49.685
- We came back after dinner together.
- I see.

00:53:49.768 --> 00:53:50.811
I'm sleeping over here.

00:53:50.894 --> 00:53:52.771
Why? You have a home of your own.

00:53:52.855 --> 00:53:55.566
To chat with you and stuff.

00:53:55.649 --> 00:53:57.651
- Is Hyeonggeun asleep?
- He fell asleep just now.

00:53:57.735 --> 00:53:59.194
- Don't wake him up.
- Auntie is here.

00:54:04.992 --> 00:54:06.452
Why are you in a daze?

00:54:07.411 --> 00:54:08.829
Is Seokcheol coming late today?

00:54:09.455 --> 00:54:11.915
He's on a trip. He texted me.

00:54:11.999 --> 00:54:13.876
What trip all of a sudden?

00:54:24.094 --> 00:54:25.387
Horrible wench.

00:54:53.248 --> 00:54:57.336
We're leaving in five minutes.
Go take care of your needs if you have to.

00:54:58.170 --> 00:55:01.256
- I'm going to the bathroom, sir.
- Okay, go on.

00:56:01.275 --> 00:56:04.111
MYOUNGSAN - JEONGSEON

00:56:12.661 --> 00:56:13.829
<i>Seokkyung,</i>

00:56:13.912 --> 00:56:17.332
<i>Hyeonggeun has been praying</i>
<i>that you'll come home</i>

00:56:17.416 --> 00:56:19.585
<i>when the lilac tree starts blooming.</i>

00:56:55.954 --> 00:56:59.791
It's said that
every star is the light of the past.

00:57:00.459 --> 00:57:02.628
Some are the lights from years ago.

00:57:02.711 --> 00:57:06.465
And some are the lights
from hundreds of years ago,

00:57:06.548 --> 00:57:07.924
traveling all the way here.

00:57:09.051 --> 00:57:12.054
Thus, the past and present are connected.

00:57:14.806 --> 00:57:16.141
I believed

00:57:16.725 --> 00:57:18.560
we'd meet again someday.

00:57:19.978 --> 00:57:22.564
I thought it'd be nice
to run into you on the street

00:57:23.231 --> 00:57:27.736
or pass you by in a moving car.

00:57:29.655 --> 00:57:33.325
And when I actually met you again,

00:57:33.408 --> 00:57:34.910
I was so happy

00:57:36.536 --> 00:57:38.038
that my wish came true.

00:57:42.876 --> 00:57:44.795
It wasn't just your wish.

00:57:45.837 --> 00:57:47.255
My prayer was answered too.

00:57:52.219 --> 00:57:55.013
Let's never part ways again,
no matter what happens.

00:57:56.765 --> 00:57:58.141
Let's never part ways again.

00:58:58.201 --> 00:58:59.911
Hyeonggeun!

00:59:02.330 --> 00:59:03.749
Hyeonggeun!

00:59:05.083 --> 00:59:06.835
Ms. Jo Maksoon!

00:59:10.338 --> 00:59:11.339
Mom?

00:59:12.048 --> 00:59:13.884
Mr. Park Silgon!

00:59:15.719 --> 00:59:17.053
Your foolish daughter

00:59:17.888 --> 00:59:19.806
is back home!

00:59:21.683 --> 00:59:22.684
Mom!

00:59:29.065 --> 00:59:30.609
Father!

00:59:31.276 --> 00:59:32.486
Mom!

00:59:33.445 --> 00:59:35.197
Hyeonggeun!

00:59:44.498 --> 00:59:46.583
Hyeonggeun!

00:59:53.840 --> 00:59:56.009


01:00:21.326 --> 01:00:22.494
The Nice Guy

01:00:23.078 --> 01:00:24.746

<i>Go in and beg him for forgiveness.</i>

01:00:24.830 --> 01:00:25.831
Dad. Seokkyung.

01:00:25.914 --> 01:00:27.457
<i>Let him cuss you out</i>
<i>and beat you up.</i>

01:00:27.541 --> 01:00:29.000
Father! No, Father!

01:00:29.084 --> 01:00:30.627
<i>Who took the order?</i>

01:00:30.710 --> 01:00:32.671
<i>Seokcheol? Are you sure about this?</i>

01:00:33.255 --> 01:00:35.215
<i>Your father</i>
<i>wants to sell this house.</i>

01:00:35.298 --> 01:00:38.718
<i>I borrowed some money</i>
<i>on this house as security.</i>

01:00:39.469 --> 01:00:41.721
<i>You must be going through a lot.</i>

01:00:41.805 --> 01:00:42.848
Is it ready?

01:00:43.598 --> 01:00:44.766
<i>We can attack right now.</i>

01:00:44.850 --> 01:00:45.851
Begin.

01:00:54.150 --> 01:00:57.696
<i>My son, Seokcheol,</i>
<i>said he'd quit.</i>

01:00:58.572 --> 01:01:00.323
<i>Let him go on a good note.</i>